    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-03-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-03-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="265" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d265">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Baker</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-03-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 14,
                            1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Did Great Britain land troops under asserted right of sovereignty or only for
                        protection? Prompt answer desired.</p>
            </div>
